setenv: [
  [ PATH += "%{hipjit:hip-runtime-path}%" ]
]
post-messages: [
  "hipjit needs the AMD HIP runtime and hiprtc libraries at run time."
  "On Linux, install ROCm (or the HIP runtime); set HIP_PATH to the install prefix if it is not /opt/rocm."
  "On Windows, install the AMD HIP SDK (the installer sets the HIP_PATH environment variable)."
  "This package puts the SDK's bin directory on PATH through opam's environment (the hip-runtime-path variable, applied via setenv), so load the opam environment -- e.g. `eval $(opam env)`, or its PowerShell equivalent -- for the amdhip64/hiprtc DLLs to be found."
]
